BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Durham Writers Group
UID:event_313514714@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260321T023238Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T213000
SUMMARY:*IN-PERSON* SF/F Group
DESCRIPTION:Durham Writers Group\nWe will be at the People's Solidarity Hu
 b at 1809 Chapel Hill Rd\, Durham. This venue does not serve food or drink
 \, but feel free to bring your own. There is a kitchenette for our use\, b
 ut be sure to clean up afterwards. The space might be a little cozy\; plea
 se consider masking or staying home if you have a respiratory ailment.\n\n
 This sub-group focuses on Speculative Fiction\, including Science Fiction\
 , Fantasy and Horror. If you have anything that falls under that category 
 — be it short story\, poem\, novel-in-progress or screenplay — then co
 me! We'd love to hear from you.\n\nOur format allows each reader 15 minute
 s to present their work aloud\, followed by approximately 20 minutes of fe
 edback from the other attendees. To ensure fairness\, each attendee is lim
 ited to 1 minute of Initial Feedback time. During that period\, the author
  remains silent. Next\, we have a 5 minute Free-For-All discussion about t
 he work -- then the author may speak. (We usually get through three reader
 s.)\n\nThough not required\, in order to receive more in-depth feed-back\,
  readers may post their work in advance on our Google Group:\nhttps://grou
 ps.google.com/d/forum/durham-sff-writers-group\n\nWe ask that participants
  keep their comments constructive and respectful\, focusing on what works 
 or doesn't work in the piece.\n\nWe also ask that readers provide a warnin
 g\, both on the Google Group and during the meeting\, if their story featu
 res content that some readers might find upsetting. This includes descript
 ions of violence or sexual content.\n\nReaders are:\n• Sagar\n• Crysti
 na\n• Ruth\nBackup Readers are:\n• Milbre\n• Rena\n• Ryan\nDeep Ba
 ckup:\n• James\n\n***\n\n***We meet every Tuesday at the same time\, but
  alternate between In-Person*** ***and on Zoom. Members may attend both fo
 rmats\, if desired\, but readers will be listed separately under the In-Pe
 rson or Zoom weeks.***
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/dwg-writers/events/313514714/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260225T002856Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260225T002856Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Durham Writers Group
UID:event_312995719@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260321T023238Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260331T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260331T213000
SUMMARY:*VIRTUAL* SF/F Group
DESCRIPTION:Durham Writers Group\n**Zoom Info Below Description**\n\nThis 
 sub-group focuses on Science Fiction and Fantasy\, so if you have anything
  that falls under that category — be it short story\, poem\, novel-in-pr
 ogress or screenplay — then come! We'd love to hear from you.\n\nOur for
 mat allows each reader 15 minutes to present their work... followed by app
 roximately 20 minutes of feedback from the other attendees. To ensure a fa
 ir opportunity to respond\, each attendee is limited to 1 minute of feedba
 ck time. (We usually get through three readers.)\n\nIf a reader elects to 
 post their work in advance (NOT a requirement!)\, members will be able to 
 access that work at our Google Group:\nhttps://groups.google.com/d/forum/d
 urham-sff-writers-group\n\nWe ask all members to provide a warning\, both 
 on the Google Group and during the meeting\, if their story features conte
 nt that some readers might find upsetting. This includes descriptions of s
 exual violence.\n\nReaders are:\n• Naveed\n• Fraser\n• Sigma\n\nBack
 up Readers are:\n• Lucy\n• Laramie\n• Rachel\n\nDeep Backup:\nRaven\
 n\n***\n\n***We meet every Tuesday at the same time\, but alternate betwee
 n meeting In-Person and on Zoom. Members may attend both formats\, if desi
 red\, but readers will be listed separately under the In-Person or Zoom we
 eks.***\n\n> Enabled for both audio and video. Users can choose what to sh
 are.\n> Users can share their screen/application\, which could be good for
  reading along.\n> There is a shareable whiteboard.\n> Users can annotate 
 the screen.\n> You can set up polls (host only?).\n\nJoin Zoom Meeting\nht
 tps://duke.zoom.us/j/640491577\n\nMeeting ID: 640 491 577\nPasscode: 00423
 4\n\nDial by your location\n+1 646 876 9923 US (New York)\n+1 253 215 8782
  US\n+1 301 715 8592 US\n\nJoin by SIP\n640491577@zoomcrc.com\n\nJoin by H
 .323\n162.255.36.11 (US East)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/dwg-writers/events/312995719/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260121T234738Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260121T234738Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
